The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to graphs and their weights, which are central topics in computer science. The use of fast matrix multiplication (FMM) suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and linear algebra (cs.DM). The reduction techniques used in the paper are also relevant to complexity theory (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.DS). Finally, the focus on minimum weight cycles and triangles suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.DS).
